Setting up cloudmqp account:

-> Open: https://customer.cloudamqp.com/signup?_gl=1*vvcbj2*_gcl_au*MTg3Mjk4MTA3Mi4xNzEwNDA3NzM0

-> To signup fill all the details 

-> Create an instance, Select the instance you want (Little Lemur - Free)
 
-> Select a region and data center (From AWS, AZURE, GCP, DigitalOcean)

-> Click on confirm to create an instance

-> You'll get a dashboard showing your instance, To use the instance remotely click on instance name and search for AMQP details and copy url

-> Now you can use the url to access the rabbitmq remotely

-> To open rabbitmq go to the instances and click on RabbitMQ Manager
